On this day in 1997, Afrobeat pioneer, Femi Anikulapo Kuti, known to the world as Fela Kuti died. He was known and revered as the activist with a lion heart. Despite facing arrest over 200 times, having his house burned down, seeing his mother thrown down from the window of his Kalakuta Republic, he fearlessly called out corrupt leaders in Nigeria. A hero of the Nigerian state, no musician has been able to tie the shoes he wore. In memory of his death, we have compiled 12 of his tracks for your reflection:         Read More: Remembering Bob Marley: Top Ten Songs    